This article is a proclamation by President Barack Obama declaring January 19, 2015, as the Martin Luther King, Jr., Federal Holiday. The proclamation pays tribute to the life and legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr., highlighting his role as a champion for justice and equality. It emphasizes the importance of economic opportunity and empathy in achieving equality. The proclamation also calls for continued vigilance in securing the gains made since Dr. King's time and emphasizes the need for good jobs, fair wages, safe neighborhoods, and quality education. The article encourages Americans to observe the holiday with civic, community, and service projects in honor of Dr. King.